Position at Triton Digital
Triton Digital® is the global technology and services leader to the digital audio and podcast industry. Operating in more than 40 countries, Triton provides innovative technology that enables broadcasters, podcasters, and online music services to build their audience, maximize their revenue, and streamline their day-to-day operations. In addition, Triton powers the global online audio industry with Webcast Metrics®, the leading online audio measurement service. With unparalleled integrity, excellence, teamwork, and accountability, Triton remains committed to connecting audio, audience, and advertisers to continuously fuel the growth of the global online industry. Triton Digital is a wholly owned subsidiary of The E.W. Scripps Company (NASDAQ: SSP).

Triton's Webcast Metrics (WCM) audience measurement service is the industry standard for audience measurement and audio consumption data. WCM provides credible, validated data that enables live and on-demand audio publishers to quantify their audience at global, national, and local levels. Portions of our Webcast Metrics data are accredited by the Media Rating Council (MRC). In addition, our data and processes are continuously audited internally, and annually by a top-tier accounting firm.

Reporting into our SVP Compliance and Industry Relations and Chief Compliance Officer, the Data Analyst will analyze data and perform other tasks as needed related to the audit and accreditation process. This position will be based from our New York office. We are open to entry level applicants with relevant IT audit educational backgrounds or experience in audit within technology firms.

Main Responsibilities:

_ Execute data trend investigations on a weekly, monthly and quarterly basis across multiple products

_ Execute live testing across different WCM measurement implementations (players, SDKs, widgets, apps, etc.) to assess the quality, and potential areas for improved measurement, across user devices and browsers

_ Execute post-implementation publisher QA procedures on newly implemented stations to be measured by WCM, including working with Triton Digital and client personnel to remediate non-compliant implementations in a timely basis

_ Prepare and present clear and concise data analyses reports to senior management as it relates to interpreting and modeling data to accommodate data presentation needs

_ Provide internal support to MRC audit inquiries as needed.

Job Requirements/Qualifications:

_ BS/BA in accounting or bachelor's degree in computer science, information systems, or related field required;

_ 2 years of experience in a related role, in auditing, data analysis or IT related field an asset;

_ Project management skills and attention to detail are critical;

_ Strong analytical, interpersonal and written/verbal communication skills;

_ Experience or interest for technology industry (online audio and/or video media experience an asset);

_ High proficiency in computer operations, especially Microsoft Word and Excel; and analytical tools, such as Looker, with willingness to expand computer skills

_ Ability to understand internal control concepts and experience in applying them to document, plan, perform and report on the evaluation of business and IT processes, areas and functions;

_ Ability to achieve results through cross-functional, virtual teams

_ Ability to prioritize and deliver on multiple projects simultaneously

_ Positive attitude, leader, team player, takes initiative, ability to work independently and manage a remote team;

_ Display a demonstrated ability to think broadly while managing the details;

_ Maturity, superior judgement and analytical skills;

_ Ability to handle confidential information discretely and always maintain confidentiality;

_ Experience with MRC and/or IAB policies and procedures is desired, but not required;

_ Some US/Canada travel may be required.
